Minister of Natural Resources and Tourism, Dr Damas Ndumbaro has met with management of three famous Spanish clubs, including La Liga giants, with the aim of signing deals to promote Tanzania’s tourism industry. A statement issued by the Ministry on Friday names the La Liga clubs involved in the discussions as Atletico Madrid and Getafe. Another club which participated in the talks was Real Valladolid Club which was set to be promoted into elite La liga League. Real Valladolid Club is owned by a former Brazil national team player, Ronaldo De Lima. Dr Ndumbaro said the club management were willing to cooperate with Tanzania in marketing its tourism. “Our main goal is to market Tanzania attractions worldwide through sports by placing adverts on jerseys of these clubs as well as billboards placed on the field,” Dr Ndumbaro said. He added that Tanzania depends on its wildlife tourism 100 per cent and that through the strategy other tourist attractions such as beach tourism, cultural tourism as well as ecological tourism will be known around the world and attract many tourists to the country.